	<body>
		<outline text="July 2021" type="calendarMonth" name="july2021" >
			<outline text="July 9" type="calendarDay" name="09" >
				<outline text="Colorado leads U.S. states with first look at new congressional districts. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.reuters.com/world/us/colorado-leads-us-states-with-first-look-new-congressional-districts-2021-06-18/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 09 Jul 2021 14:13:43 GMT" tweetId="1413501624249503748" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1413501624249503748" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="davewiner" />
				<outline text="1/3 Every time I switch my iPhone to a different computer, I have to start over with music. Why. After 15 years or so, couldn't they offer a way to back it up and then restore it? This must be some kind of copyright thing. I wish I had a phone that was rationally designed with" type="tweet" created="Fri, 09 Jul 2021 13:51:36 GMT" tweetId="1413496058047434759" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1413496058047434759" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="davewiner" >
					<outline text="2/3 the user in mind. I also have an Android phone, but as far as I can tell they broke the only way to copy music onto the device from a Mac. Not sure if a Windows machine is any better. Same reason I'd love to move my desktop act to Linux, but I can't do it without Frontier." type="tweet" created="Fri, 09 Jul 2021 13:51:38 GMT" tweetId="1413496066347986944" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1413496066347986944" inReplyToId="1413496058047434759" tweetUserName="davewiner" >
						<outline text="3/3 Which is, btw, why I had to buy a new Mac. I mistakenly updated my iPhone and it wouldn't work with the Mac I keep un-updated so I can continue to run Frontier. All I have to say is this: Oy. What a mess." type="tweet" created="Fri, 09 Jul 2021 13:51:39 GMT" tweetId="1413496070403883010" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1413496070403883010" inReplyToId="1413496066347986944" tweetUserName="davewiner" >
							<outline text="BTW, when I watch people slowly add to threads trying to make it work, I wonder why they don't just use https://t.co/KAVhNd06pG. It's a writing tool designed specifically for Twitter threads. Write it, tweak it up, look at the preview, tweak some more, publish. Boom." type="tweet" created="Fri, 09 Jul 2021 13:52:52 GMT" tweetId="1413496377016004609" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1413496377016004609" inReplyToId="1413496070403883010" tweetUserName="davewiner" />
							</outline>
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Netflix Hires Ex-Apple Executive to Lead Podcasting Operations. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2021-07-08/netflix-hires-ex-apple-executive-to-lead-podcasting-operations&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 09 Jul 2021 13:29:59 GMT" tweetId="1413490618400186369" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1413490618400186369" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="davewiner" />
				<outline text="Afghan pilots assassinated by Taliban as U.S. withdraws. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.reuters.com/world/asia-pacific/afghan-pilots-assassinated-by-taliban-us-withdraws-2021-07-09/?utm_source=twitter&amp;utm_medium=Social&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 09 Jul 2021 11:52:21 GMT" tweetId="1413466049102577668" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1413466049102577668" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="davewiner" />
				<outline text="Apple founder Steve Wozniak backs right-to-repair movement. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.bbc.com/news/technology-57763037.amp&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 09 Jul 2021 09:19:32 GMT" tweetId="1413427590212296704" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1413427590212296704" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="davewiner" />
				<outline text="Write good examples by starting with real code. &lt;a href=&quot;https://jvns.ca/blog/2021/07/08/writing-great-examples/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 09 Jul 2021 08:08:36 GMT" tweetId="1413409738566610946" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1413409738566610946" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="davewiner" />
				</outline>
