				<outline text="&quot;Critical Race Theory&quot; == &quot;Willie Horton&quot;

&lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Willie_Horton&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 07 Jul 2021 20:07:33 GMT" tweetId="1412865895379124226" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1412865895379124226" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="davewiner" />
				<outline text="What's your favorite scene in The Matrix?" type="tweet" created="Wed, 07 Jul 2021 19:04:06 GMT" tweetId="1412849924497186825" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1412849924497186825" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="davewiner" >
					<outline text="Mine is when the oracle says you’re cute, I see why she likes you. Neo says who? Oracle says Not too bright, though. Kind of like the great scene from as good as it gets where the mother says that’s what we all want dear, it doesn’t exist." type="tweet" created="Wed, 07 Jul 2021 23:48:10 GMT" tweetId="1412921411975450625" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1412921411975450625" inReplyToId="1412849924497186825" tweetUserName="davewiner" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="After all we've been through, Covid, the Insurrection, the fires and hurricanes, it amazes me how little imagination has crept into American political discourse." type="tweet" created="Wed, 07 Jul 2021 18:57:53 GMT" tweetId="1412848361967960066" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1412848361967960066" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="davewiner" />
				<outline text="after all we've been through, covid, the insurrection, it amazes me how little imagination has crept into american political discourse." type="tweet" created="Wed, 07 Jul 2021 18:56:48 GMT" tweetId="1412848087123607558" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1412848087123607558" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="davewiner" />
				<outline text="A new toolkit for OPML support. 

&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/opmlPackage&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;

Node and browser-based code to read and write OPML files. Makes it easy for outliners and tools to interop. 

We say no to silos. ❤️" type="tweet" created="Wed, 07 Jul 2021 18:51:56 GMT" tweetId="1412846863762460679" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1412846863762460679" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="davewiner" >
					<outline text="An 18-minute podcast that explains why I did this OPML toolkit for JavaScript, now. 

https://t.co/2USUym9g9r" type="tweet" created="Thu, 08 Jul 2021 13:58:52 GMT" tweetId="1413135498055327757" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1413135498055327757" inReplyToId="1412846863762460679" tweetUserName="davewiner" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="1/2 About Trump's claim that Twitter and Facebook are obligated by the First Amendment, I'm not sure that's wrong. If a social network is so large that they effectively control all speech in a channel, if there's no way around them, different rules should apply." type="tweet" created="Wed, 07 Jul 2021 18:41:15 GMT" tweetId="1412844175255556099" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1412844175255556099" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="davewiner" >
					<outline text="2/2 On the other hand, speech, even as guaranteed by the government, is not an absolute. The Constitution is not a suicide pact, President Lincoln said." type="tweet" created="Wed, 07 Jul 2021 18:41:17 GMT" tweetId="1412844183367344139" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1412844183367344139" inReplyToId="1412844175255556099" tweetUserName="davewiner" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="I was asked &quot;What is an outliner?&quot; 

An outliner is a text editor that organizes information in a hierarchy, allowing users to control the level of detail and to reorganize according to structure.

Much more here...

https://t.co/s2RAlWp8nd

#toolsforthought" type="tweet" created="Wed, 07 Jul 2021 13:10:27 GMT" tweetId="1412760928148459524" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1412760928148459524" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="davewiner" />
