				<outline text="For an all-too-brief window, New York belonged to New Yorkers. #giftlink &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/07/02/nyregion/new-york-city-tourism.html?unlocked_article_code=AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACEIPuonUktbfqohkT1UbASbTTMIqoRyBg7_JzaN5l3jkL22eSCpTivgSHpKB4EKLZbZmY5F7-QWnc-J7Ee1lQu1unKgYNlZxSgKsr9zdxslfLnw58se5VDM8ms_GUeh9oDXjZCznJuwvm-zv7hzZaTL6SeeIhy1aUQVkoZZic1qtyCZIkv-DSrgpr4E4ifQxBZl6RSMCYj2Iu5TrDBZ8MNaFanLM-1V8GrEZCXyIw4nqu_9Xex5SCFnFUHp6_W43jdtYM9ocN677RAUyAVQFQcjsiMiAM7S90sNQNw&amp;smid=url-share&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 05 Jul 2021 16:09:59 GMT" tweetId="1412081333560647685" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1412081333560647685" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="davewiner" />
				<outline text="It's impossible to understate how slavery formed the politics of the United States to this day.

We don't think it has because we were told in school that it's in our past. 

The truth is, the losing side of the Civil War never conceded." type="tweet" created="Mon, 05 Jul 2021 16:04:02 GMT" tweetId="1412079835267088392" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1412079835267088392" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="davewiner" >
					<outline text="understate should be overstate. oy. 😍" type="tweet" created="Mon, 05 Jul 2021 17:15:26 GMT" tweetId="1412097801434152966" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1412097801434152966" inReplyToId="1412079835267088392" tweetUserName="davewiner" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="America’s politics appear to be stubbornly fixed. That's like saying someone with the flu has a high temperature. The actual problem is the US had a genetic defect at birth that makes it seemingly impossible for it to be united. Slavery.  &lt;a href=&quot;https://politicalwire.com/2021/07/05/americas-politics-are-stubbornly-fixed/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 05 Jul 2021 15:11:20 GMT" tweetId="1412066571472756739" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1412066571472756739" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="davewiner" >
					<outline text="This is the big picture.

I'd like to inject this into the global discussion.

It isn't just America's problem, our slavery was part of Europe's exploitation of Africa too. 

We are raised with the self-image of our parents and grandparents. That's how this continues." type="tweet" created="Mon, 05 Jul 2021 15:25:53 GMT" tweetId="1412070234371117059" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1412070234371117059" inReplyToId="1412066571472756739" tweetUserName="davewiner" >
						<outline text="Every generation starts with the assumption that everything will change because of them. Some have it stronger than others. But it's always wrong. We are formed by our parents, even if we don't think we are." type="tweet" created="Mon, 05 Jul 2021 15:25:53 GMT" tweetId="1412070235344146432" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1412070235344146432" inReplyToId="1412070234371117059" tweetUserName="davewiner" />
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="If you think &lt;a href=&quot;https://archive.org/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; is backing up your stuff, check it out, see if they really are." type="tweet" created="Mon, 05 Jul 2021 13:51:01 GMT" tweetId="1412046361877532678" urltweet="https://twitter.com/davewiner/status/1412046361877532678" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="davewiner" />
